SIMPLE: openly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Openly
<hw>O"pen*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>openlice</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>In an open manner; publicly; not in private; without
secrecy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How grossly and <qex>openly</qex> do many of us contradict the
precepts of the gospel by our ungodliness!</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without reserve or disguise; plainly;
evidently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My love . . . shall show itself more <qex>openly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>open-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
